adually dismantled by the region's advancing market economy, colonial modes of constructing power and social identity have lingered on even to this day.The result of painstaking research in remote rural archives, some of them now made inaccessible by the Shining Path, Mirages of Transition will become the definitive work on the Peruvian highlands.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Latin America / General.2bisacsh  aadministration.  aandean plateau.  aargentina.  abolivia.  abusiness development.  acapitalism.  acase study.  achile.  acollao.  acolonialism.  acultural studies.  aeconomic analysis.  ahigh altitude.  ainstitutional history.  alake titicaca.  alatin america.  alatin american history.  amarket economy.  aperu.  aperuvian altiplano.  aperuvian highlands.  aperuvian history.  aplains.  apolitics.  apower.  arural andes.  arural.  ashining path.  asocial analysis.  asocial identity.  asouth america.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052008291540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520913912?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520913912423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520913912/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles